{"id": "EUVD-2022-26770", "enisaUuid": "86680a92-64b8-35fe-9580-fba0fc561f9c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nscsi: target: Fix WRITE_SAME No Data Buffer crash\n\nIn newer version of the SBC specs, we have a NDOB bit that indicates there\nis no data buffer that gets written out. If this bit is set using commands\nlike \"sg_write_same --ndob\" we will crash in target_core_iblock/file's\nexecute_write_same handlers when we go to access the se_cmd->t_data_sg\nbecause its NULL.\n\nThis patch adds a check for the NDOB bit in the common WRITE SAME code\nbecause we don't support it. And, it adds a check for zero SG elements in\neach handler in case the initiator tries to send a normal WRITE SAME with\nno data buffer.", "datePublished": "2025-05-02T21:52:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-23T13:19:46", "baseScore": 7.7, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2022-21546.html", "https://git.kernel.org/linus/ccd3f449052449a917a3e577d8ba0368f43b8f29", "https://lore.kernel.org/all/20220628022325.14627-2-michael.christie@oracle.com/", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-21546", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ccd3f449052449a917a3e577d8ba0368f43b8f29", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4226622647e3e5ac06d3ebc1605b917446157510", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/54e57be2573cf0b8bf650375fd8752987b6c3d3b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d8e6a27e9238dd294d6f2f401655f300dca20899", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00007.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-21546"], "assigner": "oracle", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0596fd04-7dd0-3d91-88c6-d411682358ee", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f6970ad31d42fceb38b5595cbad093a4d0bfcc43 <ccd3f449052449a917a3e577d8ba0368f43b8f29"}, {"id": "0baa5902-47d6-3483-a745-96490073f3e8", "product": {"name": "Oracle Linux"}, "product_version": "Oracle Lin